# Python Code Quality Standards

## Pylint target: 10.00/10

After every substantive edit run pylint on changed files:

```bash
.venv/bin/pylint <changed_file_or_package> --score=yes
```

If score drops below 10.00, fix all reported issues before finishing.

## Docstrings — required everywhere public

Every public module, class, and method must have a docstring.
Private helpers (`_name`) are exempt but encouraged.

```python
# BAD — missing docstring on public method
def run(self) -> QueueResults:
    ...

# GOOD
def run(self) -> QueueResults:
    """Compute E[T] and E[W] averaged over the job-size distribution."""
    ...
```

## ASCII-only source files

Python source files must contain only ASCII characters.
Use ASCII equivalents in docstrings and comments — never paste Unicode math symbols:

| Instead of | Write |
|---|---|
| `ρ_x`, `λ`, `∫` | `rho_x`, `lam`, `int` |
| `≥`, `≤` | `>=`, `<=` |
| `→`, `—` | `->`, `--` |

## No imports inside functions

Lazy imports (`import` inside a function body) are forbidden.
Move all imports to the module top level.

```python
# BAD
def get_pdf(t):
    from scipy.stats import norm  # C0415
    return norm.pdf(t)

# GOOD — import at module level
from scipy.stats import norm

def get_pdf(t):
    return norm.pdf(t)
```

## Type hints on all public signatures

```python
# BAD
def conditional_mean_response(self, x):
    ...

# GOOD
def conditional_mean_response(self, x: float) -> float:
    ...
```

## Distribution API consistency

All `Distribution` subclasses in `most_queue.random.distributions` must
expose `get_pdf(params, t: float) -> float` and `get_cdf(params, t: float) -> float`
as static methods. Do **not** add private PDF/CDF helpers elsewhere — extend
the distribution class instead.

## No nested quadrature for repeated inner integrals

When an inner integral appears inside an outer `quad` call, precompute it
on a grid with `cumulative_trapezoid` + `np.interp` instead of calling
`quad` again for every outer evaluation point.

```python
# BAD — O(n²) nested quad
def outer(x_max):
    quad(lambda x: f(x) * quad(lambda t: ..., 0, x)[0], 0, x_max)

# GOOD — precompute grid, look up with np.interp
grid_xs = np.linspace(0, x_max, 2000)
grid_int = cumulative_trapezoid(integrand(grid_xs), grid_xs, initial=0)
quad(lambda x: f(x) * np.interp(x, grid_xs, grid_int), 0, x_max)
```
